==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Petal
<hw>Pet"al</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧t"⟦ait⟧l; 277)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>pe`talon</grk> a leaf, a leaf or plate of metal, fr.
<grk>pe`talos</grk> outspread, broad, flat: cf. F.
<ets>p⟦eacute⟧tale</ets>. See <er>Fathom</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>One of the leaves of the corolla, or the colored
leaves of a flower. See <er>Corolla</er>, and <xex>Illust.</xex> of
<er>Flower</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>One of the expanded ambulacra
which form a rosette on the black of certain Echini.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Petaled</ent>⟦br⟧
